Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Sonoma Index-Tribune is a 5,300-circulation newspaper covering all of Sonoma and Sonoma Valley. Founded in 1879, the paper is now published twice weekly, on Tuesdays and Fridays, and also produces a website at www.sonomanews.com, a news bulletin emailed to subscribers seven days a week, and several social media feeds. Located 40 miles north of San Francisco in Northern California’s premier Wine Country, Sonoma Valley — Jack London’s famous “Valley of the Moon” — is 18 miles long, extending from the San Pablo Bay north to Kenwood. The City of Sonoma — built around a green, tree-filled plaza designed by Sonoma’s founder, General Mariano Vallejo — is the Valley’s cultural and business center. Volume 1, Number 1, the first issue of the Sonoma Index, was published here in Sonoma on April 17, 1879. In 1884, Harry Granice, great-grandfather of longtime publishers Bill and Jim Lynch, purchased the paper and renamed it the Sonoma Index-Tribune. The Index-Tribune is now owned by Sonoma Media Investments, Inc., which also owns the Press Democrat, the Petaluma Argus-Courier, the North Bay Business Journal and Sonoma Magazine.

We are conveniently located in downtown El Cajon with easy access to the 8, 67, and 125. We use 100% natural wax that include 100% Organic Beeswax (hard wax), Eucalyptus Oil infused soft wax, and our very own 100% natural sugar wax (sugaring). By taking advantage of the physical properties each wax has to offer, we use are able to identify which wax is best suited for specific areas of the body. Our emphasis is not only on providing the best possible results with our skin treatments, but also informing and educating everyone who comes through our doors. We value every single client and one of our top priority is customer service. We also take pride in offering the best quality products and techniques to all our clients.
